	abstract = {Monte Carlo simulations have become a useful tool for studying ion radiation effects at or near surfaces or interfaces, such as sputtering, reflection, mixing, etc. The principal advantage of Monte Carlo calculations is that any physical process can be included directly. Also multielement and multilayer targets, even complex geometries, can be treated exactly in order to simulate realistic cases.

